<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 22 at 10:53PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...HEAVY RAINFALL AND LOW VISIBILITY FOR TRAVELERS DURING THE LATE
NIGHT...
WEATHER...
* A band of showers and thunderstorms will move from western
Lower Michigan across southeast Michigan during the late night.
Rainfall will be heavy at times with localized totals in the
half inch to 1 inch range generally along a line from Flint to
Pontiac to Detroit and mainly from midnight to 3 AM.
IMPACTS...
* Low visibility for motorists.
* Ponding of water on area roadways.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Motorists are urged to use caution and account for variable
driving conditions by traveling and slower speed.
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
